## Lesson Operators 1 Arimethic & Conc
Modulo Operator - Remainder



The modulo operator represented by the percent symbol %. This operator finds the remainder that's left over after dividing one number by another.

Here's how the modulo operator works:

result = 10 % 3    -- result is 1 (10 divided by 3 is 3 with remainder 1)
result = 15 % 4    -- result is 3 (15 divided by 4 is 3 with remainder 3)
result = 8 % 2     -- result is 0 (8 divided by 2 is 4 with no remainder)
One of the most practical uses of the modulo operator is determining if a number is even or odd. When you divide any number by 2, if the remainder is 0, the number is even. If the remainder is 1, the number is odd:

number = 7
remainder = number % 2    -- remainder is 1, so 7 is odd

number = 10
remainder = number % 2    -- remainder is 0, so 10 is even
